article.description: Jaylen Adams scored 22 points with six rebounds and six assists as Saint Bonaventure beat Ohio 81-68 on Saturday.
article.headline: Saint Bonaventure beats Ohio 81-68
article.story: SAINT BONAVENTURE, N.Y. -- Jaylen Adams scored 22 points with six rebounds and six assists as Saint Bonaventure beat Ohio 81-68 on Saturday. Adams hit 7 of 12 from the field including five 3-pointers for the Bonnies (5-2). Marcus Posley had 19 points and five assists and Dion Wright posted a double-double with 14 points and 12 rebounds. Adams sank three of his 3-pointers in the first half, helping the Bonnies to a 37-35 lead at the break. Ohio's Antonio Campbell and Treg Setty combined for a 10-3 run to start the second period, giving the Bobcats (4-3) a 45-40 lead with 16:03 to play. Adams, Wright and Denzel Gregg responded with a 14-5 surge that put the Bonnies back up, 54-50, with 12:17 remaining and they never trailed after that. Campbell finished with 20 points for the Bobcats. Setty had a double-double, scoring 16 points with 12 rebounds.
